<TestCaseEntity>
   <description>As a Focused Review Coder I want to access the Details tab for a task on the Focused Review screen so that I can view Intake history for the record I want to process. 

Acceptance Criteria: 

RM-966.1: CDAT allows the user to open a Focused Review task by selecting the Coversheet ID in the Open Tab of the Central Coder Queue. 

RM-966.2: CDAT directs the user to the Focused Review screen after the coder has selected a task to work on. The Focused Review screen displays the following tabs: 
•Details (displayed by default) - Details tab is read only. 
•Code MR 

RM-966.3: CDAT provides an View Submission option for the user to view medical record documentation. 

RM-966.4: The Details tab displays the following header information: 
•Coversheet ID 
•Enrollee ID 
•Enrollee Name 
•Corrected Name 
• Enrollee DOB 
•Corrected DOB 
•Provider Type 
•Date of Service Start 
•Date of Service End 
-CHIC 
-RRBHIC 

RM-966.5: CDAT provides an option to filter by the following fields: 
• Submission Review 
• Senior Evaluation 
• Invalid Confirmation 
• Escalation 
• Escalation Resolution 
• PM Reset 

RM-966.6: CDAT displays a timeline which shows previous actions performed on the record. The latest action performed is displayed first. Note: The complete life cycle of the record is shown in Research Management. The details tab will only display comments by step based on user exclusions. 

RM-966.7: CDAT allows the user to sort the timeline from newest to oldest and vice versa. 

RM-966.8: CDAT displays a date and timestamp (MM/DD/YYYY, X:XX AM/PM EST) for each action in the timeline. 

RM-966.9: CDAT displays the following comments when applicable: 
• All comments and escalation related comments from Submission Review, Senior Evaluation and Invalid Confirmation 
• QA Panel Reset comments 
• PM Reset comment if the record was PM Reset at Focused Review 

RM-966.10: CDAT displays the user who entered each comment. 

RM-966.11: CDAT provides the option to minimize the comment(s) for each section.</description>
